spec: concurrent_futures_extra66
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html#exception-classes — Python concurrent.futures exception class documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends concurrent_futures_extra65.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __name__/__module__/__qualname__, CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor/InvalidStateError identity and bases, as_completed/wait __name__/__qualname__, FIRST_COMPLETED/FIRST_EXCEPTION/ALL_COMPLETED values and __len__(), class __module__/__name__/__len__() tables, submit/shutdown qualname lens, Future method qualname lens, class __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables, wait/__name__=='wait', as_completed/__name__=='as_completed', class __class__.__name__/__qualname__ equality, wait/__class__.__module__=='builtins', class __doc__/__class__/__module__=='builtins' tables, ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'), as_completed/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'), class __init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function'), class __repr__/__weakref__ __class__.__name__ tables, exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ tables, cf.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list'), cf.__all__.__len__()==14, __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'), cf.__all__.__contains__ membership checks, cf.__package__.__eq__('concurrent.futures'), Future/Executor __doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str'), __loader__/__spec__/__file__/__cached__ __class__.__name__, __spec__ attributes, Future/__init__ and ThreadPoolExecutor/__init__ and Future.result/done/cancel/exception and ThreadPoolExecutor.submit/shutdown __qualname__.__eq__, wait/as_completed __annotations__/__globals__ class identity, Future.__doc__.__contains__('Represents'), ThreadPoolExecutor.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') (extra59), wait/__defaults__/__code__/__class__.__name__ checks (extra60), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ __code__.co_name equality and co_argcount values (extra61), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ co_varnames/co_filename/co_flags attribute chains (extra62), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ co_consts/co_nlocals/co_stacksize type identity (extra63), wait/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='tuple', wait/__defaults__.__len__()==2, as_completed/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='tuple', as_completed/__defaults__.__len__()==1, Future.__init__/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType', executor __class__.__name__=='type' (extra64), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType', ThreadPoolExecutor/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, ProcessPoolExecutor/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, Executor/__name__/__module__, Future/__name__/__module__ (extra65)."
    - "This spec covers (cfid66 namespace): wave 235 theme — concurrent.futures exception hierarchy identity. NEW in extra66: InvalidStateError.__name__.__eq__('InvalidStateError'); InvalidStateError.__qualname__.__eq__('InvalidStateError'); InvalidStateError.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures._base'); BrokenExecutor.__name__.__eq__('BrokenExecutor'); BrokenExecutor.__qualname__.__eq__('BrokenExecutor'); BrokenExecutor.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures._base'); CancelledError.__name__.__eq__('CancelledError'); CancelledError.__qualname__.__eq__('CancelledError'); CancelledError.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures._base'); TimeoutError.__name__.__eq__('TimeoutError'); BrokenProcessPool.__name__.__eq__('BrokenProcessPool'); BrokenProcessPool.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures.process')."
    - "concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError.__name__ == 'InvalidStateError'. InvalidStateError is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py as a subclass of Error. Its __name__ is the simple class name 'InvalidStateError'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. InvalidStateError is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py. Its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__name__ == 'BrokenExecutor'. BrokenExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py as a subclass of RuntimeError. Its __name__ is the simple class name 'BrokenExecutor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. BrokenExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py. Its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__name__ == 'CancelledError'. In Python 3.8+, concurrent.futures.CancelledError is defined as a subclass of BaseException in _base.py. Its __name__ is 'CancelledError'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. CancelledError is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py. Its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.TimeoutError.__name__ == 'TimeoutError'. concurrent.futures.TimeoutError is defined in _base.py as a subclass of Exception. Its __name__ is 'TimeoutError'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenProcessPool.__name__ == 'BrokenProcessPool'. BrokenProcessPool is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py as a subclass of BrokenExecutor. Its __name__ is 'BrokenProcessPool'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenProcessPool.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures.process'. BrokenProcessPool is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py. Its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures.process'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures exception __name__ checks — extra66
#
# Wave 235 theme: exception hierarchy identity.
#
# InvalidStateError.__name__ == 'InvalidStateError'
# BrokenExecutor.__name__ == 'BrokenExecutor'
# CancelledError.__name__ == 'CancelledError'
# TimeoutError.__name__ == 'TimeoutError'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra66.exception_names_1:
  description: "concurrent.futures exception __name__.__eq__ checks in cfid66 namespace — wave 235 theme: exception hierarchy identity; InvalidStateError.__name__=='InvalidStateError'; BrokenExecutor.__name__=='BrokenExecutor'; CancelledError.__name__=='CancelledError'; TimeoutError.__name__=='TimeoutError'; NEW in extra66: first __name__.__eq__ string equality checks for these exceptions in the cfid66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: cfid66

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [invalidstate_name,  InvalidStateError.__name__.__eq__, ["InvalidStateError"], true, "InvalidStateError.__name__ == 'InvalidStateError' — concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError is defined in _base.py as a subclass of Error; its __name__ is the simple class name 'InvalidStateError'; NEW in extra66: first __name__.__eq__ check for InvalidStateError in the cfid66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [brokenexec_name,    BrokenExecutor.__name__.__eq__,    ["BrokenExecutor"],    true, "BrokenExecutor.__name__ == 'BrokenExecutor' — concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor is defined in _base.py as a subclass of RuntimeError; its __name__ is the simple class name 'BrokenExecutor'; NEW in extra66: first __name__.__eq__ check for BrokenExecutor in the cfid66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [cancelled_name,     CancelledError.__name__.__eq__,    ["CancelledError"],    true, "CancelledError.__name__ == 'CancelledError' — concurrent.futures.CancelledError is defined in _base.py as a subclass of BaseException; its __name__ is the simple class name 'CancelledError'; NEW in extra66: first __name__.__eq__ check for CancelledError in the cfid66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [timeout_name,       TimeoutError.__name__.__eq__,      ["TimeoutError"],      true, "TimeoutError.__name__ == 'TimeoutError' — concurrent.futures.TimeoutError is defined in _base.py as a subclass of Exception; its __name__ is the simple class name 'TimeoutError'; NEW in extra66: first __name__.__eq__ check for TimeoutError in the cfid66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

